<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,849,1128]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,849,875]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[281,406,850,876]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyphora">
<emphasis box="[281,406,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">C. cyphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[897,1020,850,876]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clorindaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[897,1020,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Clorindaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the crown length 0.9x or more of interocular width, aedeagus without unpaired apical process, aedeagus asymmetrical, aedeagus with pair of relatively thick apical processes sinuate but not forming semicircles in caudal view. In addition to the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blocker, H. D. &amp; Fang, Q." box="[237,501,958,984]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="341 - 346" refId="ref78364" refString="Blocker, H. D. &amp; Fang, Q. (1992) A synopsis of the Faltala group (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) with descriptions of new taxa. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 65, 341 - 346." type="journal article" year="1992">Blocker &amp; Fang (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, the species was illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zahniser, J. N. &amp; Dietrich, C. H." box="[846,1157,958,984]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 211" refId="ref82248" refString="Zahniser, J. N. &amp; Dietrich, C. H. (2013) A review of the tribes of Deltocephalinae (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 45, 1 - 211. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2013.45" type="journal article" year="2013">Zahniser &amp; Dietrich (2013)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
